U.S. brass mill copper stocks fell to185,400 short tons (copper content) at the end of January from191,200 short tons at the end of December, according to theAmerican Bureau of Metal Statistics.    Consumption by brass mills increased to 60,700 short tonsin January from 48,900 short tons in December.    Mills consumed 29,600 tons of refinery shapes in Januaryversus 24,000 tons in December. Scrap consumption increased to31,100 tons in January from 24,900 tons in December.    Total brass mill shipments increased to 69,600 tons inJanuary from 54,400 tons in December, while receipts rose to63,800 tons from 47,100 tons. Reuter&#3;